    <section id="sectionFour">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="bangerAlertOverlay col-lg-6 offset-lg-6">
          <div class="projoTwoDesc">
            <h1>DJ Song Suggestion App</h1>
            <p>A song suggestion app for 'YouTube DJs'. Once the user inputs a song the app will return a suggestion which is not only from a related artist but also rhythmically matched to the input. The app can then stack the songs in video players, allowing users to create video playlists. The most challenging part of the project was implementing heavy usage of the Spotify API and Youtube APIs, but I wanted to challenge myself to implement an an external application with functionality which really added to the experience.</p>
            <div class="links">
              <p><a href="https://github.com/mikejdegroot/wdi-london-project-1" target="_blank">GitHub</a> || <a href="https://ancient-wave-67409.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">Heroku</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="sectionFive">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="projoThreeSquare col-lg-6 up">
          <h1><span href="#sectionFive">V</span></h1>
          <div class="projoThreeIntro">
            <h1>Ecommerce App</h1>
          </div>
          <div class="projoThreeDesc hidden">
            <p>An Ecommerce site for people to buy and sell homemade products. As a group project, we wanted to create something as near to a real-world site as possible, with realistic functionality and a professional feel for both buyers and sellers. Buyers can add items to their shopping basket, enter card details at the checkout. Sellers can receive orders and mark them as shipped. I was responsible for the orders functionality which presented fresh challenges in sending active orders to the relevant sellers, as well as updating their status.</p>
            <div class="links">
              <p><a href="https://github.com/alexandriako/wdi-ldn-project-3" target="_blank">GitHub</a> || <a href="https://wabi-sabi.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">Heroku</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
